<br>
His golden sun-like aura hissed about as it tried to ward off the imposing darkness. The room was filled with so much darkness it appeared as if Apollo was entrapped in a forcefield, a circular orb of magnificent golden light.<br>
<br>
Apollo trotted over to his throne to the left of Zeus's, the one he had stolen from Dionysus. A smirk played upon his lips as he sat in the throne closest to Zeus's besides Hera's herself. It made him feel important, more important than he already was. He shook the golden hair from his eyes and looked at everyone in the room, feeling more secure now that he was seated in his throne. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
