<br>
&quot;I've just come back from a hunt with Artemis if you must know. What sparks my curiosity is as to what brings you all to Olympus of all places? Is there some kind of convention the rest of us failed to know about for the past couple thousand years?&quot; he smiled to them all.<br>
<br>
The clapping of sandels on the marble drew Apollo's attension to the entrance hallway into the throne room. The sandels belonged to that of Artemis his sister who was as dark as he was light.  He smirked as she would probably be able to chat it up with most of the people in the room more easily than he could.<br>
<br>
As Artemis made her way over to Apollo the room seemed to grow lighter as their golden and silver aura's shone magnificently together. The Divine Twins were united and as it seemed not a hand would be layed upon them. Apollo's face contorted as Artemis ruffled his hair, his laurel crown fell to the side. He laughed and punched her arm playfully before sighing and resting his head in his hand. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
