<br>
&quot;Actually the hunt went quite well. I  bagged myself a huge buck, took Art and myself to pin it down and slit its throat after it fell.&quot; he displays the blood on his arm.<br>
&quot;Not my battle wound.&quot; he rubs the dried blood from his arm. Looking down at his messy attire, Apollo raised his hand and snapped. Soon the room filled with light (well as best it could under the circumstances) and Apollo appeared clean in a new black tunic, his crown sandels and jewels all of gold. <br>
<br>
Apollo's leg crossed, his sandel falling and hanging on his big toe as it bobbed back and forth. Apollo snapped and almost instantly after Hebe the cup-bearer strolled into the room with her entourage of nymphs. They all held platters with either goblets of nectar or bowls of ambrosia and platters of baklava.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just a bit of Olympian hospitality for you all.&quot; Apollo smiled and waved his hand dismissingly at the bunch as if to say &quot;proceed and enjoy&quot;. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
