</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A prophet's intuition</span><hr size=1> Apollo's ears twitched at Madmartigan whispered such things to him.His eyes also narrowed and his aura's size change significantly, it seemed to drown out the darkness more so then when he was 'calm'. A smile still graced his face, a smile full of triumph for he had ALWAYS had this sneaking suspision that Hypnos had an ace up his sleeve. Apollo knew he was waiting for everyone to show their deck, so that he could triumphantly flash his royal flush and end the game for all. Being the god of prophecy Apollo had known this, everytime he looked Hypnos in the eye, every time Hypnos smiled, he had this mask on, to his 'friends' and to his family, it was all a hoax.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you'll excuse me...&quot; Apollo said with a smile, he stood from his throne and grasped one of the arms of Madmartigan's cloak and led him into one of the many halls of Olympus. He shooks the sandy blonde hair from his eyes and inquired:<br>
<br>
&quot;You know something I don't. And I want it, you know I want it. And Madmartigan I know you know that in one way or another over the years I have helped you. And if there is anything you owe me it is to tell me what the 'Silver-footed' Hypnos has half-baked against me.&quot; his expression was not of urgency or anger, it was actually quite soft as he spoke with his friend, he knew he could foul whatever Hypnos had up his sleeve, for he was Apollo. Enough said, and no third tier god of all imaginary was going to put any kink in his plans to wind up on top.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, Mad, I am trusting you to tell me the truth. I will be able to tell if you are lying. As God of Truth I can smell a lie, or a misfabrication from a mile away. Now...let us hear this 'something' he is up to...&quot; Apollo smirked and crossed his arms. <p>     *~*The Golden God*~*
              :o: Apollo :o: 
      God of all things Divine


